{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"cdfb6d61-1f8c-4418-98e8-09e35cf8783d","content":"Yes, both are known MSTest v4 breaking changes. Here's what's happening:\n\n## 1. Lost Test History in Azure DevOps\n\nMSTest v4 changed the **test-ID generation strategy**. IDs are now fully-qualified (`Namespace.Class.Method`), so Azure DevOps sees them as new tests.\n\n**Fix:** Add a `.runsettings` file (or update your existing one) to restore the old IDs:\n\n```xml\n<RunSettings>\n  <MSTest>\n    <TestIdGenerationStrategy>Legacy</TestIdGenerationStrategy>\n  </MSTest>\n</RunSettings>\n```\n\n## 2. `TestContext.TestName` in `[ClassInitialize]`\n\nIn v4, the `TestContext` passed to `[ClassInitialize]` is a **class-level context** — no specific test is running yet, so `TestName` throws `InvalidOperationException`. In v3 it silently returned a misleading value (often the first test's name).\n\n**Fix for your code** — remove or guard the access:\n\n```csharp\n[ClassInitialize]\npublic static void ClassInit(TestContext context)\n{\n    // context.TestName is not available here in v4\n    // Use context.FullyQualifiedTestClassName instead, or\n    // move per-test logic to [TestInitialize].\n}\n```\n\n## 3. Other v4 Changes to Watch For\n\n| Area | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| **Parallel execution** | Method-level parallelism is now the default. Tests with shared state may break. Add `[Parallelizable(Scope = None)]` or configure in runsettings if needed. |\n| **`[ClassCleanup]` timing** | Now runs at end of class by default (was end of assembly in v3). |\n| **Removed deprecated APIs** | `Assert.Inconclusive` overloads, `TestContext.DataRow`, and others from the `v1` surface are gone. |\n| **Timeout behaviour** | `[Timeout]` now uses `CancellationToken` (cooperative cancellation) instead of `Thread.Abort`. Long-running code must observe cancellation. |\n| **Source-generated attributes** | Custom attributes inheriting from `TestMethodAttribute` may need updates for the new source-gen pipeline. |\n\nIf you only need the ID fix and can't change the `.runsettings` globally, you can also set the property in your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <MSTestTestIdGenerationStrategy>Legacy</MSTestTestIdGenerationStrategy>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1829bead-5fe0-49aa-b31b-3a6067d4e875","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about MSTest v4 breaking changes. Let me provide a comprehensive answer based on what I know about MSTest v4 changes. I can see their code accesses `context.TestName` in a `[ClassInitialize]` method, which is indeed a known breaking change in MSTest v4.\n\nLet me summarize the key MSTest v4 breaking changes:\n\n1. **Fully qualified test IDs** – MSTest v4 changed the default test ID format to use fully qualified names (namespace + class + method). This causes Azure DevOps (and other test reporting tools) to see them as entirely new tests, losing history. The fix is to set `<TestIdGenerationStrategy>` to `Legacy` in the runsettings, or accept the new IDs going forward.\n\n\n2. **TestContext in ClassInitialize** – In MSTest v4, the `TestContext` passed to `[ClassInitialize]` is a \"class-level\" context that doesn't have a test name since no specific test is running yet. Accessing `TestContext.TestName` throws `InvalidOperationException`, whereas v3 would return an arbitrary value (often the first test's name), which was misleading anyway.\n3. **Lifecycle changes** – The `[ClassInitialize]` and `[ClassCleanup]` methods may have different inheritance behavior defaults, so I should check if that affects how your tests are structured.\n4. **Parallel execution is now on by default** – v4 enables method-level parallelism automatically, which can surface hidden shared-state issues that weren't apparent before. There are also changes to `Assert.AreEqual` for collections and floating-point comparisons, updates to `DeploymentItem` behavior, and removal of some deprecated APIs.","outputTokens":1046,"requestId":"BD00:2CA3BD:203A41C:2478C53:6A07D57A"},"id":"9b962186-a2cc-4f92-9bad-bb7c0ec57e47","timestamp":"2026-05-16T02:25:19.035Z","parentId":"a5b82177-9cea-4cfa-be6e-c59dfc0b1bae"}
